%20of%20Intelligence%20(GUR)%20said%20it%20had%20updated%20its%20list%20of%20foreign%20equipment%20in%20Russia's%20military%20production%20to%20now%20document%20over%20260%20high-tech%20tools%20used%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-soldier-russian-tech-support-captured-russian-tank-wouldnt-work-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUralvagonzavod%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20country's%20tank%20manufacturer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20firm%20makes%20the%20T-series%20main%20battle%20tanks%20that%20form%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20Kremlin's%20armor%2C%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-refurbish-45-soviet-era-t-72-tanks-ukraine-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESoviet-era%20T-72%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20newer%20fourth-generation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-unlikely-using-best-tank-ukraine-too-costly-weapons-maker-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ET-14%20Armata.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGUR%20said%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bvast%20majority%26quot%3B%20of%20this%20foreign%20equipment%20was%20purchased%20before%202022%2C%20during%20the%2015%20years%20or%20so%20when%20Russia%20undertook%20a%20mass%20modernization%20effort%20of%20its%20military.%20That%20means%20many%20of%20these%20tools%20likely%20were%20delivered%20to%20Russia%20before%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20began%2C%20and%20wouldn't%20have%20breached%20recent%20international%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20their%20existence%20in%20Russian%20factories%20presents%20key%20areas%20of%20concern%20for%20both%20Kyiv%20and%20Moscow.%20If%20Russia%20is%20cut%20off%20from%20spare%20parts%20and%20software%20updates%2C%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-war-machine-military-defense-spending-advanced-systems-innovation-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emilitary%20production%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20deteriorate%20signif